Supporting Components Description 5

This section outlines the scope and uses of the stored procedures and related tables. The usability of the Data dictionary is also discussed in this section.

4.1             Business Process Colaberry Resort Reality (CRR) 

The DW_CRR Stored procedure creates the Dim and Fact tables in the data warehouse, performs  inserts and updates of records in the tables using the SQL merge statements, generates the logging table with the record counts for the updates and inserts and logs the time for individual loading time and total loading time for table/tables.

 

Load the Data Warehouse Process


4.2             Logging Process

The sp_DW_Logging stored procedure is used for audit purposes. It runs as a part of the DW_CRR Stored Procedure and loads its results in the DW_Logging table. Ten input and one output parameter are passed into this stored procedure.

The @Startend parameter determines if records are getting inserted or updated on the DW_Logging table.If @startend is 1 then it is going to insert records in the table which is generated from the logging start part.If @startend is 2 then it is going to update the records in the DW_Logging table which is mainly generated from the logging end part. The Logging start part sets values for three of the parameters thats been declared in the beginning of the stored proc.

Logging Process



4.3           DW_Tables

4.3.1      Overview

The DW_Tables table contains the list of  data warehouse tables .The columns in this table are Table ID (Identity Column), Table Name, Table Type and Date ( auto generated column). 




4.3.2      Dependencies

The DW_Tables table lists the table names for the data warehouse, for individual table ids which is used in the SP_DW_Logging Stored Procedure and DW_Logging table for audit purpose.

 

4.4     DW_logging (Table)

4.4.1      Overview

The DW_Logging holds the records thats getting generated from the sp_DW_Logging stored procedure. Some columns in this table are Logging id (identity column), Table id, start record count, insert record count, update record count, total run time etc.

4.4.2      Dependencies

The records in this table is depended on the usp_DW_CRR and sp_DW_Logging stored procedure.

 

4.5     vw_DW_LoggingStats

4.5.1      Overview

The vw_DW_LoggingStats View holds the stats about the run time for any specific table and the total runtime for the Data warehouse as well. Some columns in this view are table name, table type, table id, full run time, table run time etc.

4.5.2      Dependencies


The records in this view is generated from the DW_Tables and DW_Logging tables.

4.4     DW_logging (Table)

4.4.1      Overview

The DW_Logging holds the records thats getting generated from the sp_DW_Logging stored procedure. Some columns in this table are Logging id (identity column), Table id, start record count, insert record count, update record count, total run time etc.

4.4.2      Dependencies

The records in this table is depended on the usp_DW_CRR and sp_DW_Logging stored procedure.

 

4.5     vw_DW_LoggingStats

4.5.1      Overview

The vw_DW_LoggingStats View holds the stats about the run time for any specific table and the total runtime for the Data warehouse as well. Some columns in this view are table name, table type, table id, full run time, table run time etc.

4.5.2      Dependencies


The records in this view is generated from the DW_Tables and DW_Logging tables.


Refreshing the KPI Process -

The DW_Refreshing Stored procedure calculates the records based on Refresh KPI table and also stores into a KPI_Calculated table



Refreshing Periods Process

The DW_RefreshingPeriods Stored procedure is used to calculate last 24 months from Current Date, Rolling week, Previous week,

Current month, previous month, rolling 3 months, rolling 6 months and so on and loads the Date into Refresh KPI table
